subject: b'cash: Year end email'
html:
b'
As you know, we are approaching the end of another fiscal year. Friday, June 29th is the deadline for Departmental Deposits that need to be recorded in the current year.



In order to ensure that all deposits are posted to the current fiscal year, please have them delivered to the Cashier's Department by 3:00 pm on June 29th.



It is important to note that regardless of the date a deposit was created in TWADEPO, it must be delivered to the Cashiers Department and processed by Cashiers no later than June 29th for it to be recorded in Fiscal year 12.

Mike Syljuberget
Cashiers Manager-Business Affairs Office
University of Oregon
(541) 346-3164

subject: b'cash: Departmental Deposit procedures'
html:
b'
Cashiers is considering making a change to our Departmental Deposit procedures. The proposed change, beginning 07/01/14, is that departments are only required to deliver TWO copies of the Departmental Deposit form to Cashiers. One copy will be stamped and returned to the department immediately, as a verification of the deposit. The second copy will remain in Cashiers.

If you have concerns about not receiving the third copy back in campus mail with the receipt number stamped on it, or you would like to see if the deposit has been processed, you can view that information in Banner.

There are several ways to look up your receipt number. I recommend using the form TWIDEPO. In that form you can perform a search based on the deposit number (EX 1) OR your Department (EX 2).

[cid:image001.jpg at 01CF8579.06ABE7A0]

Once in TWIDEPO you will see all current unprocessed deposits.
EX 1) To perform a query you press F7 or the ? button in Banner, then type in the deposit number of the deposit that you are looking up, D00***** (ex: D0039130).


[cid:image009.jpg at 01CEB387.C60A3E40]

Then press F8 or the "execute query" button.  The receipt number for that specific deposit will show up.


[cid:image009.png at 01CE8177.B7E78DA0]

EX 2)  To look up your deposit by Department:
Use the form TWIDEPO, and hit F7 or the ? to query, and tab over to the Department column.
Enter in your Department code.


[cid:image004.jpg at 01CF8579.06ABE7A0]

[cid:image005.png at 01CF8579.06ABE7A0]Then press F8 or the execute button to retrieve your receipt number.
NOTE: searching on your Department will  list all of the deposits that your Department has ever created. If you are looking for a specific deposit you may want to narrow your search.


If you have any questions about this process, need assistance in looking up a receipt number, or you would like to provide some feedback on this proposal, please feel free to contact Cashiers (6-3154) or the Cashiers mailbox at cashiers at uoregon.edu<mailto:cashiers at uoregon.edu> .



Mike Syljuberget
Cashiers Manager-Business Affairs Office
University of Oregon
(541) 346-3164

subject: b'cash: Check endorsement stamp'
html:
b'
To all University department depositors:

The University of Oregon bank account number with US Bank has changed.  The banking information on your current check endorsement deposit stamp will need to be updated.  We appreciate your assistance with this matter, and would like to make you aware of some options for replacing or modifying your department's stamp/s:

1.       Remove the sections of the stamp plate that are no longer applicable.  This can be done with a sharp blade (box cutter, razor blade, X-Acto knife).  Simply cut out the account number and the words "U.S. BANK" (the bottom two lines of the stamp), the entire line that reads "Treasurer, State of Oregon", and the number "58005" from the fourth line down, so it will just read "UNIVERSITY OF OREGON".  You can also remove the plate, cut out the above mentioned sections with a pair of scissors, and replace the applicable sections with superglue, if it does not reattach securely on its own.



The finished stamp should read:

[Your Department Name Here  FOR DEPOSIT ONLY  UNIVERSITY OF OREGON]










2.       Order new endorsement stamp/s.  This can be done through the office supply or custom stamp company of your choice.
If you have questions about this transition, feel free to contact me.

Thank you,

Mike Syljuberget
Cashiers Manager-Business Affairs Office
University of Oregon
(541) 346-3164

subject: b'cash: Wire Transfer Information'
html:
b'
To all departments who receive funds by wire transfer:

The wire transfer information provided on the University of Oregon website has now been updated to reflect our new bank account. Please begin using this new account number immediately, and destroy any hard copies you may have that contain the account number for the old bank account. The old bank account will remain open for a transitional period of time.

Note: This new bank account will receive all wire transfers sent to the UO, regardless of whether the originating bank is domestic or international. Therefore it is no longer necessary to have two separate wire transfer information forms.

The new Wire Transfer Information form can be found at http://ba.uoregon.edu/sites/ba/files/forms/wti.pdf

Mike Syljuberget
Cashiers Manager-Business Affairs Office
University of Oregon
(541) 346-3164

subject: b'cash: Year-end deposit reminder'
html:
b'
As you know, we are approaching the end of another fiscal year.  Tuesday, June 30th is the deadline for Departmental Deposits that need to be recorded in the current year. To beat the year-end rush, it is beneficial to have your deposits delivered to Cashiers before June 30th.. In order to ensure that all deposits are posted to the current fiscal year, please have them delivered to the Cashier's Department by 3:00 pm.

It is important to note that regardless of the date a deposit was created in TWADEPO, it must be delivered to the Cashiers Department and processed by Cashiers no later than June 30th for it to be recorded in Fiscal Year 15.

Mike Syljuberget
Cashiers Manager-Business Affairs Office
University of Oregon
(541) 346-3164

subject: b'cash: Department Deposit in Transit Reminder'
html:
b'
Good morning,

The Business Affairs Office (BAO) Financial Services Department would like to remind University of Oregon (UO) personnel of the use of account code A0951 Cash-Department Deposit In Transit. For payments you have received but cannot deposit before the Cashiers' Office year-end deadline of 3:00 p.m., Thursday June 30th, please use the following procedures to record a deposit in transit.
Record the deposit in transit by JV with a June transaction date:

Debit                      Department Index               A0951 Cash-Department Deposit In Transit

Credit                     Department Index               Revenue, Unearned Revenue, Accounts Receivable, etc.

To make the physical deposit with UO Cashiers using Banner form TWADEPO the next month:

Debit                      CASH, CHEK, or CARD depending on how the payment was received
Credit                     Department Index               A0951 Cash-Department Deposit In Transit

If deposits are made with the Cashiers' Office in July that were received by your department in June, and the above procedures were not utilized, accrue the deposit with the following JV's.

To correct the FY16 activity, record the deposit in transit by JV with a June transaction date:

Debit                      Department Index               A0951 Cash-Department Deposit In Transit

Credit                     Department Index               Revenue, Unearned Revenue, Accounts Receivable, etc.

To correct the FY17 activity, reverse the entry with a July transaction date:

Debit                      Department Index               Revenue, Unearned Revenue, Accounts Receivable, etc.

subject: b'cash: Cashiers Office Move'
html:
b'
Dear Campus Colleagues,

The Cashiers Office will soon be relocating to the Thompson University Center at 720 E 13th Ave, First Floor.
Cashiers move service hours and locations:

October 27 - 28, 8 am - 5 pm - Oregon Hall, Student Billing Front Counter

October 31, 8 am - 3 pm - Oregon Hall, Student Billing Front Counter

November 1 - Closed

November 2, 8:30 am - 5 pm - Thompson University Center, First Floor

We will continue answering our main phone number (541-346-3154) throughout this period.  If you need to reach a Cashiers employee by phone, please call the main phone number.

Please note, we will not be operational on Tuesday, November 1. We encourage you to contact us if you have any pending or potential matters that are time sensitive.

We ask your help to make this a smooth transition by bringing your deposits to Cashiers at Oregon Hall by Wednesday, October 26, at 3:00 pm, if possible.

We look forward to serving you in our new location!
https://ba.uoregon.edu/move

subject: b'cash: Year-End deposit reminder'
html:
b'
Friday, June 30th is the deadline for Departmental Deposits that need to be recorded in the current year. In order to facilitate timely closing of the books, the Cashiers Department will close at 4:00PM on the 30th. To ensure that all deposits are posted to the current fiscal year, please have them delivered to the Cashier's Department by 2:00 pm. To beat the year-end rush, it is beneficial to bring your deposits to Cashiers earlier in the week.

Please note that regardless of the date a deposit was created in TWADEPO, it must be delivered to the Cashiers Department and processed by Cashiers no later than June 30th for it to be recorded in Fiscal Year 17.

Mike Syljuberget
Cashiers Manager-Business Affairs Office
University of Oregon
(541) 346-3164

subject: b'cash: Reminder: Banner 9 - FIS Departmental Deposits (TWADEPO) Demo'
html:
b'
This is a reminder to all Departmental Deposits (TWADEPO) users that the Banner 9 Demo of this object is scheduled for today in the Crater Lake room of the EMU.  While the demonstration will focus on the differences between Banner 8 and Banner 9 relative to this form, any questions about the process will be welcomed.  Registration for the course is available in MyTrack and we encourage everyone with any interest in the topic to register for the course prior to attending.

Banner 9 - FIS Departmental Deposits (TWADEPO) Demo

Thursday, December 13, 2018

3:00PM to 4:30PM

EMU Crater Lake Room



The following are some topics that will be covered during the session:

*         Banner 9 transformation update

*         Entering and viewing Departmental Deposits

*         Associated screen views



Please contact Brian Strait (x6-2387) with any questions.  We apologize for any inconvenience.

Debit                      Department Index               A0951 Cash-Department Deposit In Transit

Credit                     Department Index               Revenue, Unearned Revenue, Accounts Receivable, etc.

To correct the FY20 activity, reverse the entry with a July transaction date:

Debit                      Department Index               Revenue, Unearned Revenue, Accounts Receivable, etc.
Credit                     Department Index               A0951 Cash-Department Deposit In Transit


Please note that this account code and procedure should only be used to record payments that you have received but are unable to deposit with UO Cashiers by month end. Established cash handling procedures must be followed as indicated at http://ba.uoregon.edu/staff/cash-handling-and-departmental-deposits.

subject: b'cash: New credit card Terminal verification process'
html:
b'
Good morning,

This message is for all departments on campus who accept payments using credit card terminals.

There has been a recent upgrade at Elavon in regards to verifying an account whenever you need to call the Elavon Terminal Support number 1-800-777-7240. Below is a list of verification options that will be asked when you call that number for technical support on your terminal:

-You will be required to provide your MID (Merchant ID number), which should be on the same sticker affixed to your terminal that includes the Technical Support number.

-You will also be asked an additional verification question that may include one of the following:
  - Last 5 digits of the UO bank account your batches are deposited into: 75662
  - The date and amount of the last batch you settled.
  - The UO Federal Tax ID number: 46-4727800

You should have this information handy before you call the Technical Support number - they will ask you for your MID, and one of these other identifying questions.

If you have any questions about this, feel free to contact me.

Mike Syljuberget
Cashiers Manager-Business Affairs Office
University of Oregon
(541) 346-3164
